The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: (Required) The name of the service (up to 255 letters, numbers, hyphens, and underscores)

properties.name: task_definition
properties.description: (Required) The family and revision (family:revision) or full ARN of the task definition that you want to run in your service.

properties.name: desired_count
properties.description: (Optional) The number of instances of the task definition to place and keep running. Defaults to 0. Do not specify if using the DAEMON scheduling strategy.

properties.name: launch_type
properties.description: (Optional) The launch type on which to run your service. The valid values are EC2 and FARGATE. Defaults to EC2.

properties.name: platform_version
properties.description: (Optional) The platform version on which to run your service. Only applicable for launch_type set to FARGATE. Defaults to LATEST. More information about Fargate platform versions can be found in the AWS ECS User Guide.

properties.name: scheduling_strategy
properties.description: (Optional) The scheduling strategy to use for the service. The valid values are REPLICA and DAEMON. Defaults to REPLICA. Note that Fargate tasks do not support the DAEMON scheduling strategy.

properties.name: cluster
properties.description: (Optional) ARN of an ECS cluster

properties.name: iam_role
properties.description: (Optional) ARN of the IAM role that allows Amazon ECS to make calls to your load balancer on your behalf. This parameter is required if you are using a load balancer with your service, but only if your task definition does not use the awsvpc network mode. If using awsvpc network mode, do not specify this role. If your account has already created the Amazon ECS service-linked role, that role is used by default for your service unless you specify a role here.

properties.name: deployment_controller
properties.description: (Optional) Configuration block containing deployment controller configuration. Defined below.

properties.name: deployment_maximum_percent
properties.description: (Optional) The upper limit (as a percentage of the service's desiredCount) of the number of running tasks that can be running in a service during a deployment. Not valid when using the DAEMON scheduling strategy.

properties.name: deployment_minimum_healthy_percent
properties.description: (Optional) The lower limit (as a percentage of the service's desiredCount) of the number of running tasks that must remain running and healthy in a service during a deployment.

properties.name: enable_ecs_managed_tags
properties.description: (Optional) Specifies whether to enable Amazon ECS managed tags for the tasks within the service.

properties.name: propagate_tags
properties.description: (Optional) Specifies whether to propagate the tags from the task definition or the service to the tasks. The valid values are SERVICE and TASK_DEFINITION.

properties.name: ordered_placement_strategy
properties.description: (Optional) Service level strategy rules that are taken into consideration during task placement. List from top to bottom in order of precedence. The maximum number of ordered_placement_strategy blocks is 5. Defined below.

properties.name: health_check_grace_period_seconds
properties.description: (Optional) Seconds to ignore failing load balancer health checks on newly instantiated tasks to prevent premature shutdown, up to 2147483647. Only valid for services configured to use load balancers.

properties.name: load_balancer
properties.description: (Optional) A load balancer block. Load balancers documented below.

properties.name: placement_constraints
properties.description: (Optional) rules that are taken into consideration during task placement. Maximum number of placement_constraints is 10. Defined below.

properties.name: network_configuration
properties.description: (Optional) The network configuration for the service. This parameter is required for task definitions that use the awsvpc network mode to receive their own Elastic Network Interface, and it is not supported for other network modes.

properties.name: service_registries
properties.description: (Optional) The service discovery registries for the service. The maximum number of service_registries blocks is 1.

properties.name: tags
properties.description: (Optional) Key-value mapping of resource tags

properties.name: deployment_controller-1
properties.description: » deployment_controller
The deployment_controller configuration block supports the following:

properties.name: type
properties.description: (Optional) Type of deployment controller. Valid values: CODE_DEPLOY, ECS. Default: ECS.

properties.name: load_balancer-1
properties.description: » load_balancer
load_balancer supports the following:

properties.name: elb_name
properties.description: (Required for ELB Classic) The name of the ELB (Classic) to associate with the service.

properties.name: target_group_arn
properties.description: (Required for ALB/NLB) The ARN of the Load Balancer target group to associate with the service.

properties.name: container_name
properties.description: (Required) The name of the container to associate with the load balancer (as it appears in a container definition).

properties.name: container_port
properties.description: (Required) The port on the container to associate with the load balancer.
Note: As a result of an AWS limitation, a single load_balancer can be attached to the ECS service at most. See related docs.

properties.name: ordered_placement_strategy-1
properties.description: » ordered_placement_strategy
ordered_placement_strategy supports the following:

properties.name: type
properties.description: (Required) The type of placement strategy. Must be one of: binpack, random, or spread

properties.name: field
properties.description: (Optional) For the spread placement strategy, valid values are instanceId (or host, which has the same effect), or any platform or custom attribute that is applied to a container instance. For the binpack type, valid values are memory and cpu. For the random type, this attribute is not needed. For more information, see Placement Strategy.
Note: for spread, host and instanceId will be normalized, by AWS, to be instanceId. This means the statefile will show instanceId but your config will differ if you use host.

properties.name: placement_constraints-1
properties.description: » placement_constraints
placement_constraints support the following:

properties.name: type
properties.description: (Required) The type of constraint. The only valid values at this time are memberOf and distinctInstance.

properties.name: expression
properties.description: (Optional) Cluster Query Language expression to apply to the constraint. Does not need to be specified for the distinctInstance type. For more information, see Cluster Query Language in the Amazon EC2 Container Service Developer Guide.

properties.name: network_configuration-1
properties.description: » network_configuration
network_configuration support the following:

properties.name: subnets
properties.description: (Required) The subnets associated with the task or service.

properties.name: security_groups
properties.description: (Optional) The security groups associated with the task or service. If you do not specify a security group, the default security group for the VPC is used.

properties.name: assign_public_ip
properties.description: (Optional) Assign a public IP address to the ENI (Fargate launch type only). Valid values are true or false. Default false.
For more information, see Task Networking

properties.name: service_registries-1
properties.description: » service_registries
service_registries support the following:

properties.name: registry_arn
properties.description: (Required) The ARN of the Service Registry. The currently supported service registry is Amazon Route 53 Auto Naming Service(aws_service_discovery_service). For more information, see Service

properties.name: port
properties.description: (Optional) The port value used if your Service Discovery service specified an SRV record.

properties.name: container_port
properties.description: (Optional) The port value, already specified in the task definition, to be used for your service discovery service.

properties.name: container_name
properties.description: (Optional) The container name value, already specified in the task definition, to be used for your service discovery service.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: creation_token
properties.description: (Optional) A unique name (a maximum of 64 characters are allowed) used as reference when creating the Elastic File System to ensure idempotent file system creation. By default generated by Terraform. See Elastic File System user guide for more information.

properties.name: encrypted
properties.description: (Optional) If true, the disk will be encrypted.

properties.name: kms_key_id
properties.description: (Optional) The ARN for the KMS encryption key. When specifying kms_key_id, encrypted needs to be set to true.

properties.name: performance_mode
properties.description: (Optional) The file system performance mode. Can be either "generalPurpose" or "maxIO" (Default: "generalPurpose").

properties.name: provisioned_throughput_in_mibps
properties.description: (Optional) The throughput, measured in MiB/s, that you want to provision for the file system. Only applicable with throughput_mode set to provisioned.

properties.name: tags
properties.description: (Optional) A mapping of tags to assign to the file system.

properties.name: throughput_mode
properties.description: (Optional) Throughput mode for the file system. Defaults to bursting. Valid values: bursting, provisioned. When using provisioned, also set provisioned_throughput_in_mibps.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: file_system_id
properties.description: (Required) The ID of the file system for which the mount target is intended.

properties.name: subnet_id
properties.description: (Required) The ID of the subnet to add the mount target in.

properties.name: ip_address
properties.description: (Optional) The address (within the address range of the specified subnet) at which the file system may be mounted via the mount target.

properties.name: security_groups
properties.description: (Optional) A list of up to 5 VPC security group IDs (that must be for the same VPC as subnet specified) in effect for the mount target.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: cluster_id
properties.description: • cluster_id – (Required) Group identifier. ElastiCache converts this name to lowercase

properties.name: replication_group_id
properties.description: • replication_group_id - (Optional) The ID of the replication group to which this cluster should belong. If this parameter is specified, the cluster is added to the specified replication group as a read replica; otherwise, the cluster is a standalone primary that is not part of any replication group.

properties.name: engine
properties.description: • engine – (Required unless replication_group_id is provided) Name of the cache engine to be used for this cache cluster. Valid values for this parameter are memcached or redis

properties.name: engine_version
properties.description: • engine_version – (Optional) Version number of the cache engine to be used. See Describe Cache Engine Versions in the AWS Documentation center for supported versions

properties.name: maintenance_window
properties.description: • maintenance_window – (Optional) Specifies the weekly time range for when maintenance on the cache cluster is performed. The format is ddd:hh24:mi-ddd:hh24:mi (24H Clock UTC). The minimum maintenance window is a 60 minute period. Example: sun:05:00-sun:09:00

properties.name: node_type
properties.description: • node_type – (Required unless replication_group_id is provided) The compute and memory capacity of the nodes. See Available Cache Node Types for supported node types

properties.name: num_cache_nodes
properties.description: • num_cache_nodes – (Required unless replication_group_id is provided) The initial number of cache nodes that the cache cluster will have. For Redis, this value must be 1. For Memcache, this value must be between 1 and 20. If this number is reduced on subsequent runs, the highest numbered nodes will be removed.

properties.name: parameter_group_name
properties.description: • parameter_group_name – (Required unless replication_group_id is provided) Name of the parameter group to associate with this cache cluster

properties.name: port
properties.description: • port – (Optional) The port number on which each of the cache nodes will accept connections. For Memcache the default is 11211, and for Redis the default port is 6379. Cannot be provided with replication_group_id.

properties.name: subnet_group_name
properties.description: • subnet_group_name – (Optional, VPC only) Name of the subnet group to be used for the cache cluster.

properties.name: security_group_names
properties.description: • security_group_names – (Optional, EC2 Classic only) List of security group names to associate with this cache cluster

properties.name: security_group_ids
properties.description: • security_group_ids – (Optional, VPC only) One or more VPC security groups associated with the cache cluster

properties.name: apply_immediately
properties.description: • apply_immediately - (Optional) Specifies whether any database modifications are applied immediately, or during the next maintenance window. Default is false. See Amazon ElastiCache Documentation for more information. (Available since v0.6.0)

properties.name: snapshot_arns
properties.description: • snapshot_arns – (Optional) A single-element string list containing an Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of a Redis RDB snapshot file stored in Amazon S3. Example: arn:aws:s3:::my_bucket/snapshot1.rdb

properties.name: snapshot_name
properties.description: • snapshot_name - (Optional) The name of a snapshot from which to restore data into the new node group. Changing the snapshot_name forces a new resource.

properties.name: snapshot_window
properties.description: • snapshot_window - (Optional, Redis only) The daily time range (in UTC) during which ElastiCache will begin taking a daily snapshot of your cache cluster. Example: 05:00-09:00

properties.name: snapshot_retention_limit
properties.description: • snapshot_retention_limit - (Optional, Redis only) The number of days for which ElastiCache will retain automatic cache cluster snapshots before deleting them. For example, if you set SnapshotRetentionLimit to 5, then a snapshot that was taken today will be retained for 5 days before being deleted. If the value of SnapshotRetentionLimit is set to zero (0), backups are turned off. Please note that setting a snapshot_retention_limit is not supported on cache.t1.micro or cache.t2.* cache nodes

properties.name: notification_topic_arn
properties.description: • notification_topic_arn – (Optional) An Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of an SNS topic to send ElastiCache notifications to. Example: arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:012345678999:my_sns_topic

properties.name: az_mode
properties.description: • az_mode - (Optional, Memcached only) Specifies whether the nodes in this Memcached node group are created in a single Availability Zone or created across multiple Availability Zones in the cluster's region. Valid values for this parameter are single-az or cross-az, default is single-az. If you want to choose cross-az, num_cache_nodes must be greater than 1

properties.name: availability_zone
properties.description: • availability_zone - (Optional) The Availability Zone for the cache cluster. If you want to create cache nodes in multi-az, use preferred_availability_zones instead. Default: System chosen Availability Zone.

properties.name: preferred_availability_zones
properties.description: • preferred_availability_zones - (Optional, Memcached only) A list of the Availability Zones in which cache nodes are created. If you are creating your cluster in an Amazon VPC you can only locate nodes in Availability Zones that are associated with the subnets in the selected subnet group. The number of Availability Zones listed must equal the value of num_cache_nodes. If you want all the nodes in the same Availability Zone, use availability_zone instead, or repeat the Availability Zone multiple times in the list. Default: System chosen Availability Zones. Detecting drift of existing node availability zone is not currently supported. Updating this argument by itself to migrate existing node availability zones is not currently supported and will show a perpetual difference.

properties.name: tags
properties.description: • tags - (Optional) A mapping of tags to assign to the resource
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: (Optional) The name of the ELB. By default generated by Terraform.

properties.name: name_prefix
properties.description: (Optional, Forces new resource) Creates a unique name beginning with the specified prefix. Conflicts with name.

properties.name: access_logs
properties.description: (Optional) An Access Logs block. Access Logs documented below.

properties.name: availability_zones
properties.description: (Required for an EC2-classic ELB) The AZ's to serve traffic in.

properties.name: security_groups
properties.description: (Optional) A list of security group IDs to assign to the ELB. Only valid if creating an ELB within a VPC

properties.name: subnets
properties.description: (Required for a VPC ELB) A list of subnet IDs to attach to the ELB.

properties.name: instances
properties.description: (Optional) A list of instance ids to place in the ELB pool.

properties.name: internal
properties.description: (Optional) If true, ELB will be an internal ELB.

properties.name: listener
properties.description: (Required) A list of listener blocks. Listeners documented below.

properties.name: health_check
properties.description: (Optional) A health_check block. Health Check documented below.

properties.name: cross_zone_load_balancing
properties.description: (Optional) Enable cross-zone load balancing. Default: true

properties.name: idle_timeout
properties.description: (Optional) The time in seconds that the connection is allowed to be idle. Default: 60

properties.name: connection_draining
properties.description: (Optional) Boolean to enable connection draining. Default: false

properties.name: connection_draining_timeout
properties.description: (Optional) The time in seconds to allow for connections to drain. Default: 300

properties.name: tags
properties.description: (Optional) A mapping of tags to assign to the resource.
Exactly one of availability_zones or subnets must be specified: this determines if the ELB exists in a VPC or in EC2-classic.
Access Logs (access_logs) support the following:

properties.name: bucket
properties.description: (Required) The S3 bucket name to store the logs in.

properties.name: bucket_prefix
properties.description: (Optional) The S3 bucket prefix. Logs are stored in the root if not configured.

properties.name: interval
properties.description: (Optional) The publishing interval in minutes. Default: 60 minutes.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: (Optional) Boolean to enable / disable access_logs. Default is true
Listeners (listener) support the following:

properties.name: instance_port
properties.description: (Required) The port on the instance to route to

properties.name: instance_protocol
properties.description: (Required) The protocol to use to the instance. Valid values are HTTP, HTTPS, TCP, or SSL

properties.name: lb_port
properties.description: (Required) The port to listen on for the load balancer

properties.name: lb_protocol
properties.description: (Required) The protocol to listen on. Valid values are HTTP, HTTPS, TCP, or SSL

properties.name: ssl_certificate_id
properties.description: (Optional) The ARN of an SSL certificate you have uploaded to AWS IAM. Note ECDSA-specific restrictions below. Only valid when lb_protocol is either HTTPS or SSL
Health Check (health_check) supports the following:

properties.name: healthy_threshold
properties.description: (Required) The number of checks before the instance is declared healthy.

properties.name: unhealthy_threshold
properties.description: (Required) The number of checks before the instance is declared unhealthy.

properties.name: list description
HTTP
properties.description: , HTTPS - PORT and PATH are required

properties.name: TCP
properties.description: , SSL - PORT is required, PATH is not supported

properties.name: interval
properties.description: (Required) The interval between checks.

properties.name: timeout
properties.description: (Required) The length of time before the check times out.

properties.name: note-on-ecdsa-key-algorithm
properties.description: » Note on ECDSA Key Algorithm

If the ARN of the ssl_certificate_id that is pointed to references a certificate that was signed by an ECDSA key, note that ELB only supports the P256 and P384 curves. Using a certificate signed by a key using a different curve could produce the error ERR_SSL_VERSION_OR_CIPHER_MISMATCH in your browser.
NOTE: At least one jdbc_target or s3_target must be specified.

properties.name: delete_behavior
properties.description: (Optional) The deletion behavior when the crawler finds a deleted object. Valid values: LOG, DELETE_FROM_DATABASE, or DEPRECATE_IN_DATABASE. Defaults to DEPRECATE_IN_DATABASE.

properties.name: update_behavior
properties.description: (Optional) The update behavior when the crawler finds a changed schema. Valid values: LOG or UPDATE_IN_DATABASE. Defaults to UPDATE_IN_DATABASE.

properties.description: (Optional) The AZ to start the instance in.

properties.description: (Optional) The Placement Group to start the instance in.

properties.name: tenancy
properties.description: (Optional) The tenancy of the instance (if the instance is running in a VPC). An instance with a tenancy of dedicated runs on single-tenant hardware. The host tenancy is not supported for the import-instance command.

properties.name: host_id
properties.description: (optional) The Id of a dedicated host that the instance will be assigned to. Use when an instance is to be launched on a specific dedicated host.

properties.name: cpu_core_count
properties.description: (Optional) Sets the number of CPU cores for an instance. This option is only supported on creation of instance type that support CPU Options CPU Cores and Threads Per CPU Core Per Instance Type

properties.name: cpu_threads_per_core
properties.description: (Optional
NOTE: Changing cpu_core_count and/or cpu_threads_per_core will cause the resource to be destroyed and re-created.

properties.name: ebs_optimized
properties.description: (Optional) If true, the launched EC2 instance will be EBS-optimized. Note that if this is not set on an instance type that is optimized by default then this will show as disabled but if the instance type is optimized by default then there is no need to set this and there is no effect to disabling it. See the EBS Optimized section of the AWS User Guide for more information.

properties.name: disable_api_termination
properties.description: (Optional) If true, enables EC2 Instance Termination Protection

properties.name: instance_initiated_shutdown_behavior
properties.description: (Optional) Shutdown behavior for the instance. Amazon defaults this to stop for EBS-backed instances and terminate for instance-store instances. Cannot be set on instance-store instances. See Shutdown Behavior for more information.

properties.name: instance_type
properties.description: (Required) The type of instance to start. Updates to this field will trigger a stop/start of the EC2 instance.

properties.name: get_password_data
properties.description: • get_password_data - (Optional) If true, wait for password data to become available and retrieve it. Useful for getting the administrator password for instances running Microsoft Windows. The password data is exported to the password_data attribute. See GetPasswordData for more information.

properties.name: monitoring
properties.description: • monitoring - (Optional) If true, the launched EC2 instance will have detailed monitoring enabled. (Available since v0.6.0)

properties.name: security_groups

NOTE: If you are creating Instances in a VPC, use vpc_security_group_ids instead.

properties.description: (Optional, VPC only) A list of security group IDs to associate with.

properties.name: iam_instance_profile

properties.name: update

properties.name: block-devices
properties.description: » Block devices

Each of the *_block_device attributes control a portion of the AWS Instance's "Block Device Mapping". It's a good idea to familiarize yourself with AWS's Block Device Mapping docs to understand the implications of using these attributes.
The root_block_device mapping supports the following:

properties.name: volume_type
properties.description: (Optional) The type of volume. Can be "standard", "gp2", "io1", "sc1", or "st1". (Default: "standard").

properties.name: volume_size
properties.description: (Optional) The size of the volume in gibibytes (GiB).

properties.name: iops
properties.description: (Optional) The amount of provisioned IOPS. This is only valid for volume_type of "io1", and must be specified if using that type

properties.name: delete_on_termination
properties.description: (Optional) Whether the volume should be destroyed on instance termination (Default: true).
Modifying any of the root_block_device settings requires resource replacement.
Each ebs_block_device supports the following:

properties.name: device_name
properties.description: The name of the device to mount.

properties.name: snapshot_id
properties.description: (Optional) The Snapshot ID to mount.

properties.name: volume_type
properties.description: (Optional) The type of volume. Can be "standard", "gp2", or "io1". (Default: "standard").

properties.name: volume_size
properties.description: (Optional) The size of the volume in gibibytes (GiB).

properties.name: iops
properties.description: (Optional) The amount of provisioned IOPS. This must be set with a volume_type of "io1".

properties.name: delete_on_termination
properties.description: (Optional) Whether the volume should be destroyed on instance termination (Default: true).

properties.name: encrypted
properties.description: (Optional) Enables EBS encryption on the volume (Default: false). Cannot be used with snapshot_id.

NOTE: Currently, changes to the ebs_block_device configuration of existing resources cannot be automatically detected by Terraform. To manage changes and attachments of an EBS block to an instance, use the aws_ebs_volume and aws_volume_attachment resources instead. If you use ebs_block_device on an aws_instance, Terraform will assume management over the full set of non-root EBS block devices for the instance, treating additional block devices as drift. For this reason, ebs_block_device cannot be mixed with external aws_ebs_volume and aws_volume_attachment resources for a given instance.
Each ephemeral_block_device supports the following:

properties.name: device_name
properties.description: The name of the block device to mount on the instance.

properties.name: virtual_name
properties.description: (Optional) The Instance Store Device Name (e.g. "ephemeral0").

properties.name: no_device
properties.description: (Optional) Suppresses the specified device included in the AMI's block device mapping.

Each AWS Instance type has a different set of Instance Store block devices available for attachment. AWS publishes a list of which ephemeral devices are available on each type. The devices are always identified by the virtual_name in the format "ephemeral{0..N}".

properties.name: network-interfaces
properties.description: » Network Interfaces

Each of the network_interface blocks attach a network interface to an EC2 Instance during boot time. However, because the network interface is attached at boot-time, replacing/modifying the network interface WILL trigger a recreation of the EC2 Instance. If you should need at any point to detach/modify/re-attach a network interface to the instance, use the aws_network_interface or aws_network_interface_attachment resources instead.
The network_interface configuration block does, however, allow users to supply their own network interface to be used as the default network interface on an EC2 Instance, attached at eth0.
Each network_interface block supports the following:

properties.name: device_index
properties.description: (Required) The integer index of the network interface attachment. Limited by instance type.

properties.name: network_interface_id
properties.description: (Required) The ID of the network interface to attach.

properties.name: delete_on_termination
properties.description: (Optional) Whether or not to delete the network interface on instance termination. Defaults to false. Currently, the only valid value is false, as this is only supported when creating new network interfaces when launching an instance.

properties.name: credit-specification
properties.description: » Credit Specification
NOTE: Removing this configuration on existing instances will only stop managing it. It will not change the configuration back to the default for the instance type.
Credit specification can be applied/modified to the EC2 Instance at any time.
The credit_specification block supports the following:

properties.name: cpu_credits
properties.description: (Optional) The credit option for CPU usage. Can be "standard" or "unlimited". T3 instances are launched as unlimited by default. T2 instances are launched as standard by default.

properties.name: example
properties.description: » Example

resource "aws_vpc" "my_vpc" {
  cidr_block = "172.16.0.0/16"

  tags = {
    Name = "tf-example"
  }
}

resource "aws_subnet" "my_subnet" {
  vpc_id            = "${aws_vpc.my_vpc.id}"
  cidr_block        = "172.16.10.0/24"
  availability_zone = "us-west-2a"

  tags = {
    Name = "tf-example"
  }
}

resource "aws_network_interface" "foo" {
  subnet_id   = "${aws_subnet.my_subnet.id}"
  private_ips = ["172.16.10.100"]

  tags = {
    Name = "primary_network_interface"
  }
}

resource "aws_instance" "foo" {
  ami           = "ami-22b9a343" # us-west-2
  instance_type = "t2.micro"

  network_interface {
    network_interface_id = "${aws_network_interface.foo.id}"
    device_index         = 0
  }

  credit_specification {
    cpu_credits = "unlimited"
  }
}

Password must contain at least 8 chars and contain at least one uppercase letter, one lowercase letter, and one number.

properties.name: master_username
properties.description: • master_username - (Required unless a snapshot_identifier is provided) Username for the master DB user.

properties.name: cluster_security_groups
properties.description: • cluster_security_groups - (Optional) A list of security groups to be associated with this cluster.

properties.name: vpc_security_group_ids
properties.description: • vpc_security_group_ids - (Optional) A list of Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) security groups to be associated with the cluster.

properties.description: • cluster_subnet_group_name - (Optional) The name of a cluster subnet group to be associated with this cluster. If this parameter is not provided the resulting cluster will be deployed outside virtual private cloud (VPC).

properties.name: availability_zone
properties.description: • availability_zone - (Optional) The EC2 Availability Zone (AZ) in which you want Amazon Redshift to provision the cluster. For example, if you have several EC2 instances running in a specific Availability Zone, then you might want the cluster to be provisioned in the same zone in order to decrease network latency.

properties.name: preferred_maintenance_window
properties.description: • preferred_maintenance_window - (Optional) The weekly time range (in UTC) during which automated cluster maintenance can occur. Format: ddd:hh24:mi-ddd:hh24:mi

properties.name: cluster_parameter_group_name
properties.description: • cluster_parameter_group_name - (Optional) The name of the parameter group to be associated with this cluster.

properties.name: automated_snapshot_retention_period
properties.description: • automated_snapshot_retention_period - (Optional) The number of days that automated snapshots are retained. If the value is 0, automated snapshots are disabled. Even if automated snapshots are disabled, you can still create manual snapshots when you want with create-cluster-snapshot. Default is 1.

properties.name: port
properties.description: • port - (Optional) The port number on which the cluster accepts incoming connections. The cluster is accessible only via the JDBC and ODBC connection strings. Part of the connection string requires the port on which the cluster will listen for incoming connections. Default port is 5439.

properties.name: cluster_version
properties.description: • cluster_version - (Optional) The version of the Amazon Redshift engine software that you want to deploy on the cluster. The version selected runs on all the nodes in the cluster.

properties.name: allow_version_upgrade
properties.description: • allow_version_upgrade - (Optional) If true , major version upgrades can be applied during the maintenance window to the Amazon Redshift engine that is running on the cluster. Default is true

properties.name: number_of_nodes
properties.description: • number_of_nodes - (Optional) The number of compute nodes in the cluster. This parameter is required when the ClusterType parameter is specified as multi-node. Default is 1.

properties.name: publicly_accessible

properties.name: encrypted

properties.description: » logging

properties.name: enable
properties.description: (Required) Enables logging information such as queries and connection attempts, for the specified Amazon Redshift cluster.

properties.name: bucket_name
properties.description: (Optional, required when enable is true) The name of an existing S3 bucket where the log files are to be stored. Must be in the same region as the cluster and the cluster must have read bucket and put object permissions. For more information on the permissions required for the bucket, please read the AWS documentation

properties.name: s3_key_prefix
properties.description: (Optional) The prefix applied to the log file names.

properties.name: snapshot_copy-1
properties.description: » snapshot_copy

properties.name: destination_region
properties.description: (Required) The destination region that you want to copy snapshots to.

properties.name: retention_period
properties.description: (Optional) The number of days to retain automated snapshots in the destination region after they are copied from the source region. Defaults to 7.

properties.name: grant_name
properties.description: (Optional) The name of the snapshot copy grant to use when snapshots of an AWS KMS-encrypted cluster are copied to the destination region.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: (Required) The name of the Redshift Subnet group.

properties.name: description
properties.description: (Optional) The description of the Redshift Subnet group. Defaults to "Managed by Terraform".

properties.name: subnet_ids
properties.description: (Required) An array of VPC subnet IDs.

properties.description: (Optional) Overwrite an existing parameter. properties.description: (Required) The CIDR block for the VPC.

properties.name: instance_tenancy
properties.description: (Optional) A tenancy option for instances launched into the VPC

properties.name: enable_dns_support
properties.description: (Optional) A boolean flag to enable/disable DNS support in the VPC. Defaults true.

properties.name: enable_dns_hostnames
properties.description: (Optional) A boolean flag to enable/disable DNS hostnames in the VPC. Defaults false.

properties.name: enable_classiclink
properties.description: (Optional) A boolean flag to enable/disable ClassicLink for the VPC. Only valid in regions and accounts that support EC2 Classic. See the ClassicLink documentation for more information. Defaults false.

properties.name: enable_classiclink_dns_support
properties.description: (Optional) A boolean flag to enable/disable ClassicLink DNS Support for the VPC. Only valid in regions and accounts that support EC2 Classic.

properties.name: assign_generated_ipv6_cidr_block
properties.description: (Optional) Requests an Amazon-provided IPv6 CIDR block with a /56 prefix length for the VPC. You cannot specify the range of IP addresses, or the size of the CIDR block. Default is false.
